spell.  You lose the advantage of horse speed, although if you have SoW or SoE, this doesn't really matter.<br>
<br>
You also do still have the disadvantage of targeting yourself via the (invisible) horse's head that takes up the middle of the screen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeddine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geddine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/02 8:09:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Medding on Horses</span><hr size=1> When sitting on a horse you are still medding as long as you are not in combat. <p><select name="GeddineChars" size="1" style="background-color: Green; color: White; font-size: xx-small; font-style: normal; font: Verdana;">
